## Security & caching headers (Netlify / Cloudflare Pages format)
## If you host on Apache, use .htaccess instead. If on Nginx, translate to add_header.

## NOTE: Framing is temporarily allowed for review/annotation tools (MarkUp.io, Pastel, Ruttl).
## BEFORE GOING LIVE: set `frame-ancestors` back to 'none' and restore `X-Frame-Options: DENY`.

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data: https://*.googleusercontent.com https://featurable.com https://*.featurable.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; script-src 'self' https://featurable.com https://*.featurable.com; connect-src 'self' https://featurable.com https://*.featurable.com; frame-src https://www.google.com https://maps.google.com; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'self' https://*.markup.io https://*.usepastel.com https://*.pastel.so https://*.ruttl.com; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  # X-Frame-Options: DENY  ← temporarily disabled for review annotation; restore before launch
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=(), interest-cohort=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
